# providers/judge.env — round-2 judge configuration for semantic code-visibility.
# Copy to providers/judge.env and set to a DIFFERENT MODEL FAMILY than the one under
# test (an independent judge; §3.2 defense-in-depth). 2024-2026 research shows a judge
# systematically favors its OWN family's outputs — including validating that family's
# WRONG answers, the exact failure this layer catches (arXiv:2508.06709 "Play Favorites";
# arXiv:2504.03846). Holds only NON-secret config: a base URL, a model id, and the NAME
# of the env var holding the judge key (never the key itself). judge.env is gitignored.
#
# Default = Groq / Llama-3.1 (Meta family) — a neutral, different family from the common
# subjects (DeepSeek, Qwen, GLM, Kimi). Verified working as an independent judge (real
# 200 + valid integer response). Change it to whatever different-family judge you have a
# key for; providers-semantic.sh WARNs if the judge endpoint equals the subject endpoint.
CMA_JUDGE_BASE_URL="https://api.groq.com/openai"
CMA_JUDGE_MODEL="llama-3.1-8b-instant"
CMA_JUDGE_KEYVAR="GROQ_API_KEY"
CMA_JUDGE_THRESHOLD="2"
